race.comment: MARHOONA (8) made her first appearance following Slipper success and got the job done against many of today's rivals last start in the 1100m Heritage at this track. Meets those runners on far better terms today. Only has to handle 1200m to be winning again. BEADMAN (1) led the Heritage field and did a good job to fight on and be beaten under a length. Made his name on rain-affected tracks as a two-year-old but flew on firmer ground last time. Sure to be prominent for a long way. GRAND EAGLE (4) had an interrupted passage behind MARHOONA a fortnight ago so his effort to get so close was full of merit. Hard to hold out over an extra furlong this time. HIDDEN MOTIVE (5) was used up early from a wide gate in the Heritage. Draws the fence this time and with a softer run may have more to offer in the closing stages. Forget the first-up run of BESKAR (3) at Moonee Valley. Trifecta and first four player with blinkers on for the first time.
